    "### 1.5 Initial Observations & Preprocessing Plan\n",
    " \n",
    "From the initial data inspection:\n",
    " \n",
    "1. **Missing values:** Only `Vehicle Type` has missing values (~67%). This is structurally expected — respondents who walk/bicycle or use public transport have no private vehicle type. We will encode this as a separate category (e.g., \"none\") rather than dropping rows.\n",
    " \n",
    "2. **Categorical encoding needed:** 13 categorical features will require encoding (ordinal or one-hot) before distance-based clustering algorithms can be applied.\n",
    " \n",
    "3. **Multi-value columns:** `Recycling` and `Cooking_With` contain list-like strings (e.g., `\"['Paper', 'Plastic']\"`) that will need parsing into binary indicator variables.\n",
    " \n",
    "4. **Scaling required:** Numerical features have very different ranges (e.g., `Vehicle Monthly Distance Km` ranges 0–2,472 vs. `Waste Bag Weekly Count` ranges 1–4). Standardisation will be necessary for distance-based algorithms.\n",
    " \n",
    "5. **CarbonEmission as validation, not input:** The `CarbonEmission` column is a calculated target. We will **exclude it from clustering input features** to discover behavioural segments organically, then use it to validate and characterise the resulting clusters.\n",
    " \n",
    "**Planned preprocessing pipeline (for upcoming milestones):**\n",
    "- Parse multi-value columns (`Recycling`, `Cooking_With`) into binary indicators\n",
    "- Fill `Vehicle Type` missing values with \"none\"\n",
    "- Apply ordinal encoding for ordered categories (e.g., shower frequency, waste bag size)\n",
    "- Apply one-hot encoding for nominal categories (e.g., diet, transport)\n",
    "- Standardise all numerical features\n",
    "- Explore dimensionality reduction (PCA) if the encoded feature space becomes very wide"
   ]
